description: One of comics' most influential and groundbreaking storytellers returns with an all-new 176-page hardcover, telling the tumultuous generational saga of a wealthy Jewish family's assimilation into New York society spanning the first half of the 1900's. It's also the story of the American Dream, and the game of marrying for social advancement. Â

Alter Ego: Centennial is a celebration of 100 issues, and 50 years, of Alter Ego, Roy Thomas' legendary super-hero fanzine. It's a double-size triple-threat book, with twice as many pages as the regular magazine, plus special features just for this anniversary edition! Behind a Rich Buckler/Jerry Ordway JSA cover, Alter Ego celebrates its dual anniversaries as Roy Thomas is interviewed about the 1990s at DC and several independents! Plus, special anniversary editions of Alter Ego staples Mr. Monster's Comic Crypt, Fawcett Collectors of America (FCA), and Alex Wright's amazing color collection of 1940s DC pinup babes!
name: Centennial

description: Hermes Press proudly announces the complete reprint of Gold Key Comics' graphic tie-in of the legendary, supernatural suspense television series, Dark Shadows, in a series of five hardcover volumes. The forerunner to today's immensely popular, vampire-themed television programs and theatrical films, Dark Shadows still garners serious attention as one of the most memorable TV shows of the last forty years. First published from 1968 to 1976, the 35 Gold Key comic books featured in this completely digitally restored collection present archetypal tales of vampires, werewolves, and the supernatural. In addition to reprinting the stories, Hermes Press will supplement each volume with poster art, pin-ups, and documentary material from the show, as well as essays about the history of Dark Shadows.
name: Volume 1

description: The story of a daddy-daughter, bounty-hunting team known as Body Bags, and this is the story of how they got together!

description: This Director's Cut edition is an expanded edition of Astonishing X-men #1 offering additional material not included in the regular edition. This volume includes script excerpts by Whedon along with design sketches by John Cassady and Gabrielle Dell 'Otto.

description: Shocking revelations and age-old foes make this collection a must-have! Batman is confronted with a hidden face from the past - it's the return of the Red Hood! With Black Mask controlling the Gotham underworld, what role will Red Hood have when all is said and done?

description:
Earth 2: Part 5 of 5

The Justice League and Crime Syndicate face annihilation at the inhuman hands of Brainiac! With the fate of two worlds in the balance, will the League discover that the only way to win... is to lose?

Green Lantern: Secret Origin: Part 5 of 7

Hector Hammond has Hal Jordan at his mercy, not to mention Carol Ferris. Will the new Green Lantern even survive long enough to investigate the death of Abin Sur alongside famed Corps member Sinestro? Plus - witness the origin of one of Green Lantern's most fearsome villains: Black Hand!

The Flash: Case One: The Dastardly Death of the Rogues: Part 4 of 6

It's Flash versus Captain Boomerang in the heart of Central City, with the Renegades on one side and the Rogues on the other! Plus - what does the Top have to tell Barry about Iris that will change everything?
name: JLA - THE END FOR EARTH 2?

description:
Son of Superman: Part 1 of 4

It's the day after tomorrow. The Justice League have been reduced to paid-up government lackeys, and Superman has been missing for years. Jon Kent thinks he's ordinary... but all that's about to change!

Green Lantern: Secret Origin: Part 6 of 7

With their rings drained of power, Hal Jordan and Sinestro go toe-to-toe with the greatest of the Five Inversions - Atrocitus! Is there any way they can hold out long enough to bring this intergalactic felon to justice? And what's with that William Hand guy, anyway?

The Flash: Case One: The Dastardly Death of the Rogues: Part 5 of 6

Has time-travelling supercop The Top really switched sides? No time to worry about that now, not when the Flash has the Rogues and the Renegades battling it out downtown. With Iris in danger, he needs to get the situation under control - and fast!
name: GREEN LANTERN - RED RAGE!

description:
Earth 2: Part 4 of 5

The Crime Syndicate are safely sealed in their moonbase by Green Lantern's power... so the JLA attempt to bring justice to a world where evil always wins. But cosmic scales always have to be balanced...

Green Lantern: Secret Origin: Part 4 of 7

Hal Jordan has only had the power ring for a week or so, and he's already travelled the universe and faced unknown terrors. But can anything prepare him for a dressing down by Green Lantern supreme, Sinestro? Plus - what's up with Hector Hammond?

The Flash: Case One: The Dastardly Death of the Rogues: Part 3 of 6

One the run from the Reverse Flash Task Force, Barry Allen has a lot of things on his mind. But perhaps he should have been paying more attention to the resurrected Digger Harkness - AKA Captain Boomerang!
name: MURDER IN MIND! - THE FLASH

description:
The Punisher is usually the most homicidal guy in town, but today Spider-Man wants him DEAD! Why has Spidey turned so blood-thirsty, and can the Punisher survive his attack?!

Also: The Inhumans face some harsh decisions in the tragic aftermath of the Kree/Shiâar War! Who will rule the galaxy? Find out here!

Plus: The Mighty Avengers face treachery as Stature tries to expose Lokiâs lies! Guest-starring the Young Avengers!

Includes material reprinted from Punisher Annual #1, War of Kings: Who Will Rule? #1 and Mighty Avengers #28.
name: SPIDER-MAN vs THE PUNISHER!

description: Acclaimed novelist Greg Rucka (A Fistful of Rain) and artist Jesus Saiz, the creative team behind The Omac Project, reunite to tell the tale of Checkmate, a covert organization that exists to keep the super-powered factions in the DC Universe "in check" regardless of national boundary, affiliation or agenda. After the explosive events of Infinite Crisis and The Omac Project, the United Nations formed this new agency to bring down heroes and villains that get out of line in a world that's more dangerous than ever. Now Checkmate uses unique abilities to deputize human and metahuman forces throughout the world.
name: A King's Game

Story Description - Taanda, White Princess of the Jungle, raised by Chief Upatani when her missionary parents died, pledged herself to protect the veldt against evil-doers, but now she was faced with a greater danger than savage beasts or scavenger hordes; invaders from the "Iron Curtain", intending to take over the Kraals from the natives, to lay waste the country, to swallow its wealth--a terrifying spine-chilling menage --- The Army of Terror!

Black Death

Table of Contents Description - From out of the slimy mire of Africa's swamps they came -- an army of dreaded insects that overran the veldt and swept away everything in their path! Taanda struggled to save a terrified jungle from... "The Ant Invasion!"

Story Description - From out of the rotted slime and damp labyrinths of Africa's swamps they came -- this army of dreaded insects, to overrun the veldt and sweep everything away in their path! Where would they go? What was their purpose? These were the questions Taanda, the White Princess, asked herself as she struggled to save a terrified jungle from a horror only she could stop --- the horror of... The Ant Invasion!

The Blue Gorilla!

Table of Contents Description - Three men and a girl hunted an animal which could bring them fame, fortune and scientific recognition. But they did not realize that it could also bring them Death! For this was... "Karth -- The Blue Gorilla!"

Story Description - Africa -- the dark continent -- land of mystery -- a land that still jealously guards its secrets! Three men and a girl set out to find a legendary creature that could bring them fame, fortune and scientific recognition -- but they did not realize that it could also bring them death -- for the natives knew of its superhuman strength and uncanny intelligence and called it Karth, The Cunning --- The Blue Gorilla!

description: Action and intrigue abound as Checkmate clashes with a rival agency on American soil and The Black Queen deputizes the big guns in an all-out bid to keep Pawn 502's mission alive! And Fire, the Black King's Knight, tries to break free from Amanda Waller's blackmail in a move that will shake the agency from top to bottom!
name: Pawn Breaks

description: By Michael Turner, Frank Mastromauro, Michael Gunnell & Jason Gorder. Everyday we're faced with choices. Left or Right? Stop or go? Love or hate? Yes or no? With each decision affecting our life, our fate. But what if those choices affected more than that, like the fate of the universe? What if they already do? What would you choose? From Michael Turner, the creative mind that brought you Fathom and Soulfire, comes the next wondrous step in comic book entertainment! For every right, there is a wrong. For every action, there is a reaction. For every up, there is a down. And for every decision Theo makes, there is someone making the decisions for hiM - and all of us! Welcome to Perspecta, and the reasons behind your wildest thoughts and darkest desires. If you thought you knew anything about our world, think again! Collecting together Shrugged Volume 1 in its entirety, including the sold out Preview and Beginnings issue, along with issues #0 through #8, with an extensive cover gallery featuring artwork by series artist Micah Gunnell, along with creator Michael Turner and a host of others, this jam packed collection is not to be missed!Â  Â  Â
name: Shrugged

description: Doctor Vincent Morrow, excommunicated from the medical community, is called upon to begin a new career in the black arts to combat supernatural monsters that prey on humanity. Morrow serves the world as it's protector, it's Witch Doctor.
name: Interview With The Tapeworm
Star of Stage, Screen and Radio
Ashcan edition

description: Mike Wolfer delivers an all-new gore-filled tale of zombie mayhem! When the contagion began in rural America, we were instructed to flee to the cities. When the cities became inundated, they became veritable death traps. Nowhere was safe and there was nowhere to run to escape the evil of the living dead. Now, the fight for life is reduced to desperation, as a group of refugees clings to the hope that sanctuary lies deep in the alligator-infested bayous of Antebellum Louisiana. But that hope is about to be dashed, because their fortified mansion stronghold on an abandoned sugar plantation becomes the very thing that lures the undead out of the swamps... That, and the tantalizing smell of tender, human flesh!

volume.name: Night of the Living Dead Annual

description: A team made up of heroes from the present and legends from the past, the JSA finds themselves fighting their history and their future, as they face off against the mad Obsidian, son of Alan Scott, the original Green Lantern and member of the Justice Society. and just as Starman, Hourman, Star Spangled Kid, Black Canary, Atom Smasher and Sand begin to recover from this emotional and physical battle, they find themselves pitted against their old foes, the Injustice Society, and the time-warlord Extant, the man responsible for the death of several members of the original Justice Society.
name: Darkness Falls

description: Just like crime, gambling doesn't pay... especially when you're gambling at The House! This volume collects JSA #26-32 plus a 5-page story from JSA: SECRET FILES #2 by Johns and Derek Aucoin, with a new cover by Michael Bair (HAWKMAN). Roulette runs the most dangerous gambling den on Earth â a club where costumed adventurers are lured to fight for their lives while super-villains bet on the outcome. Now she's turned her sights on the JSA, and she's got more than a professional interest in seeing the team destroyed! Will the JSA's survival come down to a roll of the dice?

In the action-packed JSA: STEALING THUNDER, the world's original super-hero team loses one of their most beloved teammates in a costly campaign to save the world from an insane conqueror. Taking possession of Johnny Thunder, the body-jumping Ultra-Humanite uses the hero's all-powerful Thunderbolt to create a world in which he is the supreme ruler. With most of the super-heroes under the telepathic control of the sadistic villain, a substitute JSA team consisting of Sand, Power Girl, Jakeem Thunder, and new versions of Hourman and the Crimson Avenger, must battle against the mind controlled Superman and Wonder Woman. And as the situation worsens, Captain Marvel is forced to strike a deadly blow against the Ultra-Humanite that saves the day but ultimately results in the death of the possessed Johnny Thunder.

A thrilling new trade collecting JSA 39-45! The JSA is divided, handling multiple matters in different eras. Several heroes find themselves in Ancient Egypt, fighting the immortal villain Vandal Savage and an earlier incarnation of the power of Black Adam. However, Power Girl and Dr. Mid-Nite also have their hands full with separate cases.

A new collection featuring JSA #46-55! Three of the JSA's deadliest foes band together to systematically destroy the team, clearing their way to crush mankind and rule the world! Can the JSA come together in what appears to be Earth's darkest hour?

A thrilling collection reprinting JSA #56-58 and HAWKMAN #23-25! Black Adam brings old world justice to Kahndaq as Hawkman seizes control of the JSA and brings them to the turbulent Middle East for an epic battle!

A new collection including JSA #59-67, featuring a thrilling story arc and a tie-in to IDENTITY CRISIS! The JSA visit old friends and new as they rectify injustices, aware that as they fix one problem, an even larger one is brewing in the timestream!

Don't miss a new collection featuring JSA #68-75 plus pages from 66-67! The Spectre, without a human host, is running rampant, meting out a brutal form of justice encouraged by the new Eclipso! Plus, Atom Smasher seeks forgiveness, Degaton's plan to destroy the JSA is thwarted, and more!

Collecting JSA #76-81! Following the events of DAY OF VENGEANCE, the DCU's magic-based heroes are vulnerable â and the ancient magician Mordru plans to take full advantage of the situation. Meanwhile, the fate of Atom Smasher is decided, the OMACs attack, and Green Lantern is drafted to help in an intergalactic war!

Korvac has defeated The Avengers...now the world's only hope lies with the students of the Avengers Academy, who have been grown to adults! With time manipulated, the team gets a glimpse of what the future might hold for them. For some it's a revelation...for others a life sentence! Can they overcome their personal demons and master unfamiliar abilities in time to defeat a foe powerful enough to conquer Earthâs Mightiest Heroes? Find out in the book that Newsaramaâs Best Shots calls âone of the best Avengers books â and, for that matter, one of the best Marvel books â on the stands.â
name: Put Away Childish Things

description: THIS STORY WILL BE TALKED ABOUT FOR YEARS! A new light pings into existence on Cerebra. A new mutant life is out there. A new mutant life needing Generation Hope's help, before his nascent power consumes him. Can the newest team of mutants in the world save this newest mutant? If you miss this, you only have yourself to blame.
name: The Ward, Part One

description: The Silver Surfer has always served the greater good, but with Galactusâ world-eating power at his fingertips, the High Evolutionary has his own ideas about the cosmic balance. A humbled Surfer will have to choose sides, and if he chooses poorly, the Earth is lost! The High Evolutionaryâs grand design is revealed in the continuation of the greatest cosmic tale ever told right here at home! Plus: Star-crossed romance! Which Marvel heroine claims the Surfer's heart -- and with what shocking results?
